# acquire-pins.env.example -- example --pins file for `lmde acquire`.
#
# Pass with:  lmde acquire --pins /path/to/this-file
#
# Plain KEY="value" assignments only -- no logic, no command substitution
# (acquire reads each key's last assignment). Lines beginning with # are
# comments. This is a LOCAL override for a single acquire run; acquire never
# edits this file or sandbox/pins.env.
#
# Each key pins one package to an exact published version on GitHub Packages
# (npm.pkg.github.com). A key that is ABSENT, empty, or set to the sentinel
# UNSET floats that package to the registry latest instead. So a file that
# pins only CLAI_VERSION pins clai and floats ast-mcp.
#
# Because the clai key name matches sandbox/pins.env, sandbox/pins.env is
# itself a valid --pins file: its CLAI_VERSION pins clai, and ast-mcp -- which
# has no AST_MCP_VERSION there -- floats to latest.
#
# Auth for the install is GH_AI_TOOLS_PAT, a CLASSIC PAT with the read:packages
# scope (fine-grained PATs cannot read GitHub Packages). To find a published
# version:
#   npm view @nine-at-a-time-media/clai version \
#     --registry=https://npm.pkg.github.com
# (the explicit registry is required, else npm queries registry.npmjs.org and
# fails for these private scoped packages).

# clai -- installed onto PATH (~/.local/bin/clai). Pin or float.
CLAI_VERSION="0.5.5"

# ast-mcp -- installed at ~/.local/bin/ast-mcp. Absent/UNSET here would float
# to latest; shown pinned for illustration.
AST_MCP_VERSION="0.4.0"
